Preconditions:
The input array candies must not be null.
The input array candies must not be empty.
The input array candies must only contain non-negative integers.
The value of k must be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum number of candies each child can get.
The returned value should be greater than or equal to zero.
The returned value should be less than or equal to the maximum value in the input array candies.
The returned value should be the maximum possible number of candies that each child can get, considering the value of k.